==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[middangeard|middanġeard]] ‘middle enclosure’, interpreted throughout Middle English as ‘middle earth’.

===Noun===
'''middle-earth'''
# ''(archaic)'' The physical world, as imagined between heaven and hell, or pre-Christian equivalents

